CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 9, 1960, pg. 9, reads: "Luncheon Principals - Among the principal figures who sparked Pittsburgh's 16th annual Carver Week Luncheon, held in Webster Hall's Georgian Room Tuesday of this week were, left to right: Mrs. Alma Illery, president, National Achievement Clubs Inc., sponsors: the Rt. Rev. John J. Wright, Bishop of the Pittsburgh Catholic diocese, who gave the invocation; and Dr. Ethel J. Alpenfels, New York University staff, who delivered the main address. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of five men, and four women, including Daisy Lampkin third from left, Dr. Ethel J. Alpenfels fourth from left, Alma Illery sixth from left, and Jessie Vann eighth from left, posed in Webster Hall for Carver Week luncheon
